<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 3:50PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Hartley
County through 415 PM CDT...
At 349 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Amistad, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Romero.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
